1
00:00:45,587 --> 00:00:49,967
THE INTEREST OF LOVE

2
00:01:06,692 --> 00:01:09,736
You can withdraw during the period.

3
00:01:09,820 --> 00:01:13,365
But it's necessary
that you maintain it for three years

4
00:01:13,448 --> 00:01:16,285
to be tax-exempt.

5
00:01:16,368 --> 00:01:20,330
It'd be better to keep this account
for at least three years.

6
00:01:20,664 --> 00:01:23,792
Darn it. I'm gaining more weight with age.

7
00:01:23,875 --> 00:01:27,212
Sang-su, maybe
you can teach me how to play hockey.

8
00:01:27,296 --> 00:01:28,338
Have you skated before?

9
00:01:28,422 --> 00:01:30,257
Yes, when I was little.

10
00:01:30,340 --> 00:01:32,050
At those old roller rinks?

11
00:01:33,093 --> 00:01:35,595
Do you think I'm that old?

12
00:01:49,401 --> 00:01:50,652
-Hello.
-Hi.

13
00:01:51,653 --> 00:01:53,905
You should stop by the bank sometime.

14
00:01:54,823 --> 00:01:57,117
Mr. Ha, you became an assistant manager!

15
00:01:58,285 --> 00:01:59,911
Hold on for a second.

16
00:01:59,995 --> 00:02:01,705
-That's okay.
-No.

17
00:02:01,788 --> 00:02:04,041
Take some of this home.

18
00:02:04,124 --> 00:02:06,001
Gosh. Thank you.

19
00:02:06,084 --> 00:02:07,252
-Enjoy.
-Okay.

20
00:02:07,336 --> 00:02:08,462
-Thank you.
-No worries.

21
00:02:08,545 --> 00:02:10,047
-I'll stop by soon.
-Okay.

22
00:02:15,886 --> 00:02:18,597
WHAT DO YOU WANT TO FORGET?

23
00:02:18,680 --> 00:02:21,642
THINGS THAT I WANT TO REMEMBER FOREVER

24
00:02:40,577 --> 00:02:42,913
<i>Some nights,</i>
<i>I forget about her completely.</i>

25
00:02:45,499 --> 00:02:49,002
<i>But on other nights,</i>
<i>I can see her clearly.</i>

26
00:02:52,255 --> 00:02:53,298
<i>And just like that,</i>

27
00:02:55,300 --> 00:02:56,760
<i>four years passed by.</i>

28
00:03:01,723 --> 00:03:06,395
THE INTEREST OF LOVE

29
00:03:10,524 --> 00:03:12,943
FINALE

30
00:03:15,112 --> 00:03:16,071
<i>Hello?</i>

31
00:03:16,154 --> 00:03:17,114
Goodness!

32
00:03:21,660 --> 00:03:23,495
Be careful. You're due any moment now.

33
00:03:23,578 --> 00:03:26,790
This is my third one.
Don't worry. I won't give birth here.

34
00:03:26,873 --> 00:03:28,625
-Is everyone here?
-They're in their seats.

35
00:03:28,708 --> 00:03:30,502
Mr. Lee is taking care of the groom.

36
00:03:30,585 --> 00:03:35,257
Gosh. What's gotten into him?
I guess he finally grew up.

37
00:03:36,216 --> 00:03:37,342
-Let's go inside.
-Okay.

38
00:03:37,426 --> 00:03:41,263
My goodness. Those turned out great!

39
00:03:59,531 --> 00:04:00,991
Did you get your makeup done?

40
00:04:03,243 --> 00:04:04,369
I don't need it.

41
00:04:04,453 --> 00:04:07,080
Why not? You should look good.

42
00:04:09,374 --> 00:04:11,877
If you're ready, shall we get going?

43
00:04:26,725 --> 00:04:29,519
<i>We are gathered here today</i>
<i>to celebrate the union</i>

44
00:04:29,603 --> 00:04:32,856
<i>of Ma Du-sik and Bae Eun-jeong.</i>

45
00:04:32,939 --> 00:04:36,610
<i>Please give a big round of applause</i>
<i>to the very happy couple.</i>

46
00:04:38,528 --> 00:04:40,489
<i>Please welcome the bride and groom.</i>

47
00:04:59,299 --> 00:05:02,511
For four years,
they went through the drama

48
00:05:02,594 --> 00:05:04,638
of breaking up and getting back together.

49
00:05:04,721 --> 00:05:06,473
But now they're married.

50
00:05:06,556 --> 00:05:10,227
I'm more surprised
that you're still a bachelor, Mr. Lee.

51
00:05:10,310 --> 00:05:11,228
Is that so?

52
00:05:11,311 --> 00:05:14,397
I'm more shocked that
you're pregnant with your third child.

53
00:05:14,481 --> 00:05:16,233
Trying to win an award
for having many kids?

54
00:05:16,316 --> 00:05:17,943
Watch what you say.

55
00:05:18,026 --> 00:05:22,322
I have severe mood swings at the moment
because of my hormones.

56
00:05:23,073 --> 00:05:26,827
And I'm depressed,
thanks to being on maternity leave.

57
00:05:26,910 --> 00:05:29,538
Mr. Ha, it's been a while.
Have you been well?

58
00:05:29,621 --> 00:05:32,249
Yes. Congratulations on your pregnancy.

59
00:05:33,500 --> 00:05:35,293
Are you at the Sangan branch?

60
00:05:35,377 --> 00:05:37,671
I'm going to the Yeomnam branch next week.

61
00:05:37,754 --> 00:05:39,798
The Yeomnam branch?

62
00:05:39,881 --> 00:05:41,675
I know someone who works there.

63
00:05:41,758 --> 00:05:44,719
She got a position transfer and moved
to the General Consultation Team.

64
00:05:44,803 --> 00:05:46,388
I see.

65
00:05:49,599 --> 00:05:51,268
What about you, Mr. So?

66
00:05:52,644 --> 00:05:54,271
I'm still at the Youngpo branch.

67
00:05:56,314 --> 00:06:00,735
I don't think human resources
know that you exist, Gyeong-pil.

68
00:06:00,819 --> 00:06:03,989
I mean, how else could he stay
in one place for so long?

69
00:06:04,072 --> 00:06:06,199
My goal is to become a branch manager.

70
00:06:07,492 --> 00:06:10,996
The food is good,

71
00:06:11,788 --> 00:06:14,124
but I'm craving <i>galbitang.</i>

72
00:06:14,207 --> 00:06:16,418
Didn't you have breakfast,
Deputy Manager Noh?

73
00:06:19,921 --> 00:06:23,800
I saw this coming,
so I wore my new name tag.

74
00:06:23,883 --> 00:06:26,011
It's so small. Is it legible? Look.

75
00:06:26,094 --> 00:06:26,970
"Branch Manager Noh."

76
00:06:28,388 --> 00:06:31,391
Your wife must be ecstatic
that you got a promotion.

77
00:06:32,601 --> 00:06:34,102
She's making me breakfast again.

78
00:06:34,185 --> 00:06:36,313
The last time she did that
was when we were newlyweds.

79
00:06:39,482 --> 00:06:42,319
So how have you been, Si-gyeong?

80
00:06:47,115 --> 00:06:48,033
What?

81
00:06:48,617 --> 00:06:51,578
He retired ages ago.

82
00:06:51,661 --> 00:06:53,872
I can't keep calling him
Branch Manager Yuk.

83
00:06:53,955 --> 00:06:55,290
I'm the new branch mana…

84
00:06:56,166 --> 00:07:00,295
It'd be weird
to address him any other way.

85
00:07:00,378 --> 00:07:01,588
Is that okay with you?

86
00:07:01,671 --> 00:07:03,006
Of course.

87
00:07:04,507 --> 00:07:06,509
I've been interested
in doing housework these days.

88
00:07:06,593 --> 00:07:08,637
It suits me surprisingly well.

89
00:07:10,096 --> 00:07:14,476
It's wonderful to see everyone
from the Youngpo branch again.

90
00:07:14,559 --> 00:07:17,228
-Let's enjoy the meal.
-Yes, enjoy.

91
00:07:17,312 --> 00:07:18,939
Goodness.

92
00:07:19,022 --> 00:07:20,774
Thank you for coming.

93
00:07:20,857 --> 00:07:22,275
Youngpo branch forever!

94
00:07:22,359 --> 00:07:23,652
-Forever!
-Forever!

95
00:07:23,735 --> 00:07:26,446
Congratulations on getting married.

96
00:07:26,529 --> 00:07:29,407
Thanks to my promotion,
I was able to give you

97
00:07:29,491 --> 00:07:31,326
a substantial amount
of congratulatory money.

98
00:07:31,409 --> 00:07:34,120
-Thank you, Branch Manager Noh.
-Don't mention it.

99
00:07:34,204 --> 00:07:35,413
I'm starving.

100
00:07:36,373 --> 00:07:37,999
I can't do this whole wedding again.

101
00:07:38,083 --> 00:07:40,752
Were you planning to get married twice?

102
00:07:41,378 --> 00:07:42,587
Depends on how well you do.

103
00:07:44,214 --> 00:07:46,174
But where's Assistant Manager Park?

104
00:07:47,968 --> 00:07:49,594
Isn't she a manager now?

105
00:07:49,678 --> 00:07:51,388
That's right.

106
00:07:51,471 --> 00:07:53,807
Everyone's getting promoted except for me.

107
00:07:53,890 --> 00:07:56,184
Wait, so did she not come today?

108
00:07:57,769 --> 00:07:58,979
What?

109
00:07:59,062 --> 00:08:00,605
What's the matter?

110
00:08:04,234 --> 00:08:06,111
Goodness, are you uncomfortable, Mr. Ha?

111
00:08:07,946 --> 00:08:10,156
Why would he be uncomfortable seeing her?

112
00:08:13,201 --> 00:08:16,329
Right. They used to be in a relationship.

113
00:08:18,915 --> 00:08:19,749
I'm fine.

114
00:08:19,833 --> 00:08:22,043
See? That was years ago.

115
00:08:22,127 --> 00:08:25,338
Did you not invite Ms. Ahn?

116
00:08:26,089 --> 00:08:28,174
Have you lost touch
with her after she quit?

117
00:08:34,514 --> 00:08:36,433
So… Enjoy the food.

118
00:08:36,516 --> 00:08:38,893
-Okay.
-We'll come back later.

119
00:08:38,977 --> 00:08:40,395
-Congratulations.
-Thank you.

120
00:08:40,478 --> 00:08:42,522
-Please, help yourself.
-Will do!

121
00:08:49,988 --> 00:08:52,240
You'd better go, okay?

122
00:08:53,742 --> 00:08:56,244
Today will be the last time I go.

123
00:08:56,327 --> 00:08:57,537
Hey.

124
00:08:57,620 --> 00:09:01,249
I feel a sense of guilt toward you.

125
00:09:01,332 --> 00:09:03,668
Doing this once a year
is my way of making amends.

126
00:09:03,752 --> 00:09:05,628
I don't want to hear it.

127
00:09:05,712 --> 00:09:07,630
Come to Seok-hyeon's place tonight.

128
00:09:07,714 --> 00:09:09,215
I'll have to see.

129
00:09:09,299 --> 00:09:10,550
Good luck.

130
00:09:10,633 --> 00:09:12,469
-See you.
-Bye.

131
00:09:18,641 --> 00:09:19,934
Mi-gyeong!

132
00:09:22,979 --> 00:09:25,023
-Good to see you!
-Hey!

133
00:09:25,106 --> 00:09:28,526
-How have you been?
-I've been well. You?

134
00:09:31,279 --> 00:09:33,573
<i>My name is pretty common.</i>

135
00:09:34,449 --> 00:09:38,995
From now on,
whenever you hear the name "Mi-gyeong"

136
00:09:40,455 --> 00:09:42,457
or see a 500-won coin…

137
00:09:44,459 --> 00:09:46,169
you'll feel bad for me.

138
00:09:58,389 --> 00:09:59,432
It's been a long time.

139
00:09:59,516 --> 00:10:00,517
-Hi!
-Hi!

140
00:10:00,600 --> 00:10:02,018
-Are you here for the wedding?
-Yes.

141
00:10:02,102 --> 00:10:03,645
-Have you been well?
-Yes.

142
00:10:03,728 --> 00:10:05,063
-It's been so long.
-I know.

143
00:10:24,165 --> 00:10:25,625
Long time no see.

144
00:10:28,586 --> 00:10:32,132
Why are you so late?
Everyone's been waiting for you.

145
00:10:33,508 --> 00:10:35,969
One of my inspections ended late.

146
00:10:36,052 --> 00:10:36,886
I see.

147
00:10:38,138 --> 00:10:40,765
You even work on weekends.
HQ life must be different.

148
00:10:41,975 --> 00:10:44,394
How did you know that I work at HQ now?

149
00:10:48,815 --> 00:10:50,191
Let's go inside.

150
00:10:51,276 --> 00:10:52,527
Sang-su just left.

151
00:10:53,695 --> 00:10:54,988
Should I call him?

152
00:10:56,865 --> 00:10:59,742
That's okay. He's just an ex.

153
00:11:10,545 --> 00:11:11,963
<i>So you went to Seogwang University?</i>

154
00:11:13,423 --> 00:11:14,257
Yes.

155
00:11:14,340 --> 00:11:16,509
I used to visit your school often.

156
00:11:19,220 --> 00:11:20,680
I used to go there with my ex.

157
00:11:29,689 --> 00:11:33,151
The coffee here is bitter.
Does it taste okay to you?

158
00:11:34,110 --> 00:11:37,280
I'm not very picky with coffee.
I just drink whatever.

159
00:11:39,699 --> 00:11:42,035
It's nice that you're not the picky type.

160
00:11:42,994 --> 00:11:47,123
My ex used to be
very particular about coffee.

161
00:11:55,089 --> 00:11:59,218
I'm sorry.
I don't think I can do this.

162
00:12:00,511 --> 00:12:03,431
I only showed up
because my friend insisted on it.

163
00:12:03,514 --> 00:12:07,226
But I don't think
I'm ready to start a new relationship.

164
00:12:09,896 --> 00:12:10,772
Okay.

165
00:12:27,830 --> 00:12:29,791
Let's meet up every now and then.

166
00:12:29,874 --> 00:12:32,043
We may be apart, but we're still a family.

167
00:12:32,126 --> 00:12:33,795
Let's go for round two, then.

168
00:12:34,504 --> 00:12:37,090
I have plans today. Maybe next time. Bye.

169
00:12:37,173 --> 00:12:38,383
-Bye.
-Bye.

170
00:12:38,466 --> 00:12:39,550
-Take care.
-Bye.

171
00:12:39,634 --> 00:12:41,636
-It was nice.
-I'm in the parking lot.

172
00:12:41,719 --> 00:12:42,887
-Bye.
-This was so nice.

173
00:12:46,891 --> 00:12:47,850
Aren't you leaving?

174
00:12:49,227 --> 00:12:50,228
I should.

175
00:12:56,234 --> 00:12:59,070
Do you know
what Su-yeong is up to nowadays?

176
00:13:00,989 --> 00:13:01,864
No, I don't.

177
00:13:05,159 --> 00:13:06,911
You're fine without seeing Sang-su,

178
00:13:06,995 --> 00:13:08,830
but you're curious about her.

179
00:13:10,540 --> 00:13:11,874
I guess so.

180
00:13:12,542 --> 00:13:15,545
It's strange, but I think about her
every now and then.

181
00:13:18,589 --> 00:13:19,716
Bye.

182
00:13:20,591 --> 00:13:22,093
See you next time.

183
00:13:23,302 --> 00:13:24,137
Okay.

184
00:13:40,820 --> 00:13:42,822
Aren't you transferring to another branch?

185
00:13:42,905 --> 00:13:45,950
You should get ready for that
instead of coming here.

186
00:13:47,994 --> 00:13:50,621
It's better
to get rid of the boxes when you can.

187
00:13:51,414 --> 00:13:54,333
I hate seeing you doing that
when you're all dressed up.

188
00:13:58,629 --> 00:14:02,425
You're such a great guy.
I wonder why you're still single.

189
00:14:11,893 --> 00:14:15,688
Have you still not gotten over that lady?

190
00:14:15,772 --> 00:14:16,856
Who?

191
00:14:19,233 --> 00:14:21,402
That was years ago.

192
00:14:21,486 --> 00:14:23,154
Never mind, then.

193
00:14:24,322 --> 00:14:26,949
Can you organize
the storage room while you're at it?

194
00:15:02,360 --> 00:15:04,904
Excuse me. One cup of lemon tea, please.

195
00:15:10,368 --> 00:15:12,328
One minute, please.

196
00:15:58,541 --> 00:16:00,668
-Yes?
<i>-Hey, come save me!</i>

197
00:16:00,751 --> 00:16:02,795
<i>Seok-hyeon won't let me go home again.</i>

198
00:16:02,879 --> 00:16:04,922
<i>Sang-su, where are you? Hurry up.</i>

199
00:16:05,756 --> 00:16:08,676
Just go home.
You don't have to listen to him.

200
00:16:08,759 --> 00:16:12,138
<i>I heard you got rejected</i>
<i>by your blind date today.</i>

201
00:16:12,221 --> 00:16:14,015
<i>Just come here and have a drink.</i>

202
00:16:21,105 --> 00:16:22,523
<i>I saw Mr. Ha today.</i>

203
00:16:26,194 --> 00:16:29,155
It was Mr. Ma and Ms. Bae's wedding today.

204
00:16:32,575 --> 00:16:33,743
I see.

205
00:16:35,036 --> 00:16:36,704
How is everyone?

206
00:16:37,747 --> 00:16:39,290
They haven't changed one bit.

207
00:16:40,833 --> 00:16:42,460
They were curious about you.

208
00:16:44,587 --> 00:16:47,757
But I didn't tell them anything.
I promised you that I wouldn't.

209
00:16:53,387 --> 00:16:55,014
Aren't you curious about

210
00:16:56,390 --> 00:16:57,391
how he's doing?

211
00:16:59,143 --> 00:17:00,436
You haven't asked me once.

212
00:17:04,065 --> 00:17:05,691
I think of him sometimes.

213
00:17:07,693 --> 00:17:09,779
I like that I can reminisce about him.

214
00:17:12,198 --> 00:17:13,282
Right.

215
00:17:14,617 --> 00:17:18,287
Not all love has to come true.

216
00:17:18,371 --> 00:17:22,416
And you tend to think more fondly
about that kind of love.

217
00:17:23,084 --> 00:17:27,213
But if that love comes true,
then the person you were most fond of

218
00:17:27,296 --> 00:17:31,884
suddenly becomes
the biggest nuisance in your life.

219
00:17:32,552 --> 00:17:34,178
Goodness. Look.

220
00:17:35,680 --> 00:17:37,932
It's kicking me for bad-mouthing its dad.

221
00:17:38,015 --> 00:17:39,892
What do you think you're doing?

222
00:17:42,144 --> 00:17:43,354
Gosh.

223
00:17:44,397 --> 00:17:45,648
This place is nice.

224
00:17:46,816 --> 00:17:49,819
The vibe reminds me of you.

225
00:17:50,653 --> 00:17:52,488
I bet the security deposit is pretty high.

226
00:17:53,823 --> 00:17:55,992
They want to increase it this year.

227
00:17:57,243 --> 00:17:59,662
That means you'll have to visit a bank.

228
00:18:00,997 --> 00:18:02,748
Yes. I'll need to take out a loan.

229
00:18:03,833 --> 00:18:04,792
I see.

230
00:18:06,460 --> 00:18:10,339
Then you'll probably go
to the Yeomnam branch nearby.

231
00:18:11,716 --> 00:18:12,883
Yes.

232
00:18:20,266 --> 00:18:22,018
Goodness, I should get going.

233
00:18:22,101 --> 00:18:24,186
I need to pack
for the postpartum care center.

234
00:18:24,270 --> 00:18:26,355
There's so much to prepare.

235
00:18:26,439 --> 00:18:27,773
Let me get you a cab.

236
00:18:28,733 --> 00:18:30,067
Thanks. Gosh.

237
00:18:36,532 --> 00:18:38,993
Stop drinking. You're moving tomorrow.

238
00:18:39,076 --> 00:18:41,829
Sang-su and I need to go home too.

239
00:18:43,331 --> 00:18:45,458
Should I order some <i>tangsuyuk?</i>

240
00:18:47,293 --> 00:18:48,836
I'm done eating.

241
00:18:50,254 --> 00:18:51,547
Then have a drink.

242
00:18:51,631 --> 00:18:54,175
Snap out of it, you idiot.

243
00:18:54,258 --> 00:18:56,385
How long will you keep this up?

244
00:18:56,469 --> 00:18:57,928
Why did you hit me?

245
00:18:58,971 --> 00:19:01,307
It's bad enough
that my mom hits me, damn it!

246
00:19:03,267 --> 00:19:04,477
I'm leaving.

247
00:19:05,603 --> 00:19:07,980
Where are you going?

248
00:19:11,025 --> 00:19:14,862
Take out the recycling.

249
00:19:20,368 --> 00:19:22,828
I barely managed to sell
my newlywed house after four years,

250
00:19:22,912 --> 00:19:24,914
and now I'm moving to a one-room studio!

251
00:19:24,997 --> 00:19:26,957
Take pity on me and just do it.

252
00:20:15,339 --> 00:20:18,718
<i>A past love leaves behind traces.</i>

253
00:20:31,856 --> 00:20:34,316
<i>It makes you regret</i>
<i>not making certain decisions.</i>

254
00:20:43,159 --> 00:20:45,786
<i>But it also makes you regret</i>
<i>the decisions you made.</i>

255
00:20:52,752 --> 00:20:54,837
<i>The pain isn't unbearable.</i>

256
00:21:03,512 --> 00:21:06,015
<i>But it hurts when you least expect it,</i>
<i>like a wound</i>

257
00:21:09,185 --> 00:21:10,394
<i>that won't heal.</i>

258
00:21:13,105 --> 00:21:15,316
<i>The pain is always there.</i>

259
00:21:29,163 --> 00:21:31,916
Yes, I'm on my way.

260
00:21:33,167 --> 00:21:34,168
Okay.

261
00:21:35,419 --> 00:21:37,046
All right. I'll see you soon.

262
00:21:37,880 --> 00:21:38,798
Okay.

263
00:23:02,840 --> 00:23:04,008
Excuse me.

264
00:23:09,388 --> 00:23:10,264
I'm sorry.

265
00:23:29,783 --> 00:23:32,786
