393
00:39:17,522 --> 00:39:18,690
<i>Why didn't you look for her?</i>

394
00:39:20,650 --> 00:39:24,904
Wasn't it possible to look for her
even if she didn't contact you?

395
00:39:27,782 --> 00:39:29,200
I did go to her place once.

396
00:39:31,369 --> 00:39:33,746
But she wasn't there.

397
00:39:36,082 --> 00:39:39,586
I don't think
she would've liked me to keep looking.

398
00:39:41,212 --> 00:39:42,755
Or maybe you lost confidence.

399
00:39:47,051 --> 00:39:49,345
She may have decided to ghost you,

400
00:39:51,264 --> 00:39:53,474
but maybe you gave up on her too.

401
00:39:55,602 --> 00:39:56,769
I didn't.

402
00:40:04,485 --> 00:40:05,486
Or did I?

403
00:40:22,045 --> 00:40:25,256
KCU BANK
YEOMNAM BRANCH

404
00:40:35,433 --> 00:40:37,018
Ms. Park.

405
00:40:37,101 --> 00:40:40,521
About the loan for Future Happiness
that you mentioned before…

406
00:40:48,988 --> 00:40:51,449
-Hello?
<i>-Is this Ms. Ahn Su-yeong?</i>

407
00:40:51,532 --> 00:40:53,701
<i>This is Park Seong-eun</i>
<i>from the Yeomnam branch.</i>

408
00:40:53,785 --> 00:40:55,745
Are you available today, by any chance?

409
00:40:55,828 --> 00:40:58,331
We'd like to visit you
regarding some missing documents.

410
00:40:59,248 --> 00:41:01,084
Yes, I'm free today.

411
00:41:01,167 --> 00:41:04,796
<i>Assistant Manager Ha Sang-su</i>
<i>will take over your case from now on.</i>

412
00:41:04,879 --> 00:41:06,381
<i>He'll be there shortly.</i>

413
00:41:09,258 --> 00:41:10,343
<i>Hello?</i>

414
00:41:11,469 --> 00:41:12,804
<i>Ms. Ahn?</i>

415
00:41:14,222 --> 00:41:15,348
Oh…

416
00:41:17,725 --> 00:41:18,726
Okay.

417
00:42:19,662 --> 00:42:20,997
You were here.

418
00:42:37,013 --> 00:42:38,264
Is this a café?

419
00:42:41,601 --> 00:42:42,643
Yes.

420
00:42:45,480 --> 00:42:47,899
And you can draw here as well.

421
00:43:03,247 --> 00:43:04,957
We need a few more documents.

422
00:43:07,752 --> 00:43:09,837
A statement of your rent payment

423
00:43:10,713 --> 00:43:12,423
and a certificate of VAT tax base.

424
00:43:13,674 --> 00:43:14,801
Okay.

425
00:43:19,680 --> 00:43:21,808
I'll come back
for the inspection next time.

426
00:43:24,852 --> 00:43:25,812
Okay.

427
00:43:43,538 --> 00:43:44,664
Would you…

428
00:43:49,127 --> 00:43:50,545
Would you like some coffee?

429
00:44:18,281 --> 00:44:20,199
I have to submit photos of your café.

430
00:44:22,160 --> 00:44:23,452
I see.

431
00:44:52,106 --> 00:44:53,816
Aren't you going to drink it?

432
00:44:54,525 --> 00:44:56,110
What? Right.

433
00:45:03,618 --> 00:45:05,411
Here's a wet wipe.

434
00:45:14,211 --> 00:45:15,671
Why are you laughing?

435
00:45:18,758 --> 00:45:19,759
It's just that…

436
00:45:21,552 --> 00:45:23,346
You haven't changed one bit.

437
00:45:38,277 --> 00:45:39,904
How have you been?

438
00:45:44,951 --> 00:45:46,494
What about you?

439
00:45:55,419 --> 00:45:57,129
I tried to be happy.

440
00:46:09,642 --> 00:46:11,352
What about you?

441
00:46:12,478 --> 00:46:15,189
I heard you're an assistant manager now.

442
00:46:24,073 --> 00:46:25,074
I also tried…

443
00:46:26,951 --> 00:46:28,619
to be happy.

444
00:46:42,258 --> 00:46:43,134
Why did you name

445
00:46:44,385 --> 00:46:47,847
this café Future Happiness?

446
00:46:54,103 --> 00:46:55,688
Just because.

447
00:47:05,573 --> 00:47:07,658
But I also wanted to find it.

448
00:47:13,372 --> 00:47:14,832
My future's happiness.

449
00:47:31,265 --> 00:47:33,142
I'll see you during the inspection.

450
00:47:35,352 --> 00:47:36,395
Take care.

451
00:47:38,814 --> 00:47:39,982
Okay.

452
00:49:08,362 --> 00:49:09,947
It's okay. I'm fine.

453
00:49:10,656 --> 00:49:11,532
Sit down.

454
00:49:13,033 --> 00:49:15,703
This is why people
like experienced workers.

455
00:49:15,786 --> 00:49:17,413
I gave birth very quickly.

456
00:49:17,496 --> 00:49:18,622
Congratulations.

457
00:49:20,207 --> 00:49:23,544
I heard this was
a popular caterpillar plushie.

458
00:49:23,627 --> 00:49:25,212
Goodness, thank you.

459
00:49:25,296 --> 00:49:27,298
And thank you for visiting.

460
00:49:30,217 --> 00:49:34,263
By the way,
did you bring what I asked for?

461
00:49:40,769 --> 00:49:42,146
Decaffeinated coffee.

462
00:50:00,372 --> 00:50:01,957
That hit the spot.

463
00:50:02,791 --> 00:50:05,294
I was dying to have some.

464
00:50:05,377 --> 00:50:09,006
I couldn't have any
when I was pregnant or breastfeeding.

465
00:50:09,089 --> 00:50:11,759
You made my biggest wish come true.

466
00:50:17,181 --> 00:50:20,184
By the way, did you take out that loan
at the Yeomnam branch?

467
00:50:22,686 --> 00:50:24,313
You knew, didn't you?

468
00:50:25,397 --> 00:50:27,441
That Mr. Ha was there.

469
00:50:28,442 --> 00:50:30,194
So you two met. How was it?

470
00:50:35,574 --> 00:50:36,909
I didn't feel anything.

471
00:50:38,994 --> 00:50:40,162
If that was the case,

472
00:50:40,246 --> 00:50:42,915
then why have you been
in hiding all this time?

473
00:50:48,003 --> 00:50:49,171
Su-yeong.

474
00:50:50,381 --> 00:50:53,884
Don't you think
you can be easier on yourself now?

475
00:50:55,177 --> 00:50:57,471
A lot of time has passed.

476
00:50:57,554 --> 00:51:01,600
And you're doing what you want
and making a living out of it.

477
00:51:04,520 --> 00:51:07,856
So you want me
to start a relationship with him?

478
00:51:09,650 --> 00:51:10,818
I mean…

479
00:51:10,901 --> 00:51:14,697
I'm not telling you to date someone
whom you're not interested in.

480
00:51:14,780 --> 00:51:18,575
But people who are destined for each other
will get together eventually.

481
00:51:18,659 --> 00:51:20,286
It doesn't necessarily have to be him.

482
00:51:22,413 --> 00:51:26,667
I just want you to stop
bottling everything up inside.

483
00:51:38,095 --> 00:51:40,264
It was cheese yesterday and tuna today.

484
00:51:40,889 --> 00:51:42,975
I'm so sick of <i>gimbap</i> now.

485
00:51:43,976 --> 00:51:47,479
Hey, can you make
those fried tofu rice balls again?

486
00:51:48,188 --> 00:51:49,315
Okay.

487
00:51:49,398 --> 00:51:52,067
Your girlfriend
is going to love you for your cooking.

488
00:51:55,112 --> 00:51:56,780
Are you still wearing that watch?

489
00:51:57,740 --> 00:51:59,992
You got a raise. Get a new one.

490
00:52:00,743 --> 00:52:02,536
It's still working just fine.

491
00:52:03,495 --> 00:52:05,247
But the face is cracked.

492
00:52:07,875 --> 00:52:09,084
Buy one of these.

493
00:52:10,711 --> 00:52:12,629
I don't want to throw it away.

494
00:52:13,505 --> 00:52:15,674
Why? Is there a story behind that watch?

495
00:52:16,383 --> 00:52:18,677
I'll head out first. Take your time.

496
00:54:28,849 --> 00:54:32,186
You'll be the first person I salute
when I become an officer.

497
00:54:33,520 --> 00:54:36,398
-Promise?
-Yes. I'll keep it at all costs.

498
00:55:38,335 --> 00:55:39,294
Mi-gyeong!

499
00:56:01,024 --> 00:56:04,152
INSERT COIN

500
00:56:59,791 --> 00:57:02,085
-You're here early.
-Yes.

501
00:57:05,172 --> 00:57:06,798
When did you start smoking?

502
00:57:09,885 --> 00:57:11,845
Why? You smoke too.

503
00:57:13,138 --> 00:57:14,556
I quit.

504
00:57:15,766 --> 00:57:16,975
When?

505
00:57:19,770 --> 00:57:21,355
It's been a while.

506
00:57:25,192 --> 00:57:26,193
You'll live longer, then.

507
00:57:31,990 --> 00:57:33,033
Let's go inside.

508
00:57:45,754 --> 00:57:47,923
I could've just gone to the bank.

509
00:57:50,008 --> 00:57:51,259
That's okay.

510
00:58:01,645 --> 00:58:05,273
Then everything's set now, right?

511
00:58:10,320 --> 00:58:11,238
Yes.

512
00:58:29,756 --> 00:58:30,716
Then…

513
00:58:44,479 --> 00:58:46,189
Can I paint before I go?

514
00:58:48,483 --> 00:58:50,318
I want to give it a try.

515
00:58:58,368 --> 00:59:00,954
Add a bit more shading here.

516
00:59:49,544 --> 00:59:50,587
Here.

517
00:59:51,338 --> 00:59:52,339
Right.

518
00:59:53,507 --> 00:59:54,549
Thank you.

519
00:59:56,051 --> 00:59:57,594
You did a good job.

520
00:59:58,887 --> 01:00:00,680
All I did was color.

521
01:00:02,182 --> 01:00:04,226
You're very detailed.

522
01:00:09,397 --> 01:00:11,358
What's this?

523
01:00:14,694 --> 01:00:15,695
A sand castle.

524
01:00:22,786 --> 01:00:24,538
It just looks like a mound of dirt.

525
01:00:43,640 --> 01:00:45,433
It'll be difficult to carry.

526
01:00:47,352 --> 01:00:50,021
It's okay. I brought my car.

527
01:00:57,195 --> 01:00:58,113
Well…

528
01:01:00,907 --> 01:01:03,201
Take care, then.

529
01:01:05,704 --> 01:01:06,663
Okay.

530
01:01:12,836 --> 01:01:14,296
It was nice to see you again.

531
01:01:18,508 --> 01:01:19,593
Same here.

532
01:01:31,438 --> 01:01:33,106
I hope you have a happy life.

533
01:01:36,860 --> 01:01:37,986
You too.

534
01:01:52,751 --> 01:01:55,879
I'm really going to leave now.

535
01:02:00,800 --> 01:02:01,801
Okay.

536
01:03:40,358 --> 01:03:41,901
<i>I hope you have a happy life.</i>

537
01:03:47,324 --> 01:03:48,450
You too.

538
01:04:46,132 --> 01:04:47,759
I can't believe we ran into each other.

539
01:04:50,762 --> 01:04:51,763
Me neither.

540
01:04:57,018 --> 01:04:59,062
You must be going through a rough patch.

541
01:05:05,693 --> 01:05:07,862
You said you only came here
when things got tough.

542
01:05:09,614 --> 01:05:11,491
Because this place

543
01:05:11,574 --> 01:05:14,494
-lets me know that…
-…that everything will eventually pass.

544
01:05:25,004 --> 01:05:26,464
You remembered.

545
01:05:30,552 --> 01:05:33,721
Not many people come
to such places at times like that.

546
01:05:38,518 --> 01:05:41,271
Su-yeong, why did you come here?

547
01:05:46,901 --> 01:05:49,279
I've been coming every so often.

548
01:05:55,827 --> 01:05:59,539
It's good exercise to walk around here.

549
01:05:59,622 --> 01:06:01,541
It's also quiet and empty.

550
01:06:15,013 --> 01:06:16,181
By the way,

551
01:06:18,892 --> 01:06:20,018
why don't you ask me?

552
01:06:25,231 --> 01:06:27,525
About why I ghosted you.

553
01:06:40,413 --> 01:06:42,165
Since I couldn't see you in person…

554
01:06:44,751 --> 01:06:47,337
I just asked that question
and answered it myself.

555
01:06:52,467 --> 01:06:54,719
I still don't completely understand,

556
01:06:55,762 --> 01:06:56,888
but I think…

557
01:06:57,847 --> 01:06:59,098
I somewhat understand.

558
01:07:08,358 --> 01:07:13,488
And it didn't feel right
to miss someone who broke a promise.

559
01:07:15,448 --> 01:07:16,574
What promise?

560
01:07:27,252 --> 01:07:28,294
The pork cutlets?

561
01:07:42,433 --> 01:07:43,601
How about…

562
01:07:44,686 --> 01:07:46,229
you keep that promise tomorrow?

563
01:07:59,742 --> 01:08:00,785
Sure.

564
01:08:01,911 --> 01:08:02,996
Let's do it.

565
01:08:20,179 --> 01:08:23,683
KCU BANK
YEOMNAM BRANCH

566
01:10:08,037 --> 01:10:11,833
We came through the front gate again,
but the restaurant is near the back.

567
01:10:14,585 --> 01:10:15,545
Yeah…

568
01:10:16,587 --> 01:10:19,132
The parking lot is near the front gate.

569
01:10:20,299 --> 01:10:23,177
It makes me wonder
if you really graduated from here.

570
01:10:29,809 --> 01:10:32,270
This place hasn't changed
in the past four years.

571
01:10:35,273 --> 01:10:38,651
It looked the same
when I was a student here.

572
01:10:39,819 --> 01:10:42,196
It feels like time stops
when you're at school.

573
01:10:42,822 --> 01:10:44,323
It's always the same.

574
01:10:51,414 --> 01:10:56,085
By the way, it feels really weird
to be here together.

575
01:10:59,881 --> 01:11:01,215
Same here.

576
01:11:04,427 --> 01:11:08,347
We're finally having the pork cutlets
that you bragged so much about.

577
01:11:13,311 --> 01:11:16,731
Why didn't you call me back?

578
01:11:21,736 --> 01:11:24,238
Well, why didn't you come looking for me?

579
01:11:25,615 --> 01:11:27,241
You said you could always find me.

580
01:11:30,411 --> 01:11:31,621
I did look for you.

581
01:11:32,997 --> 01:11:37,043
I went back to Tongyeong
a week after we parted ways.

582
01:11:38,711 --> 01:11:42,340
But Tongyeong was bigger
than I had thought.

583
01:11:49,180 --> 01:11:53,559
Now can you tell me why you did that?

584
01:12:01,442 --> 01:12:02,610
Because…

585
01:12:04,403 --> 01:12:06,239
there was no more to give.

586
01:12:17,792 --> 01:12:19,836
And no more to receive.

587
01:12:36,018 --> 01:12:37,812
Have you ever imagined…

588
01:12:40,439 --> 01:12:44,151
how things would've been
had you made a different decision?

589
01:12:53,703 --> 01:12:58,082
Whoever was deeper in love
doesn't have lingering thoughts like that.

590
01:13:00,209 --> 01:13:02,169
Only the one who ran away has regrets.

591
01:13:06,716 --> 01:13:09,218
You have no problem
talking about such things now.

592
01:13:11,762 --> 01:13:13,639
A lot of time has passed.

593
01:13:14,974 --> 01:13:16,601
It's only natural.

594
01:13:20,813 --> 01:13:23,608
I remember you bawling
because you liked me so much.

595
01:13:24,567 --> 01:13:26,110
What? I never did that.

596
01:13:28,738 --> 01:13:30,031
I never went that far.

597
01:13:38,789 --> 01:13:40,499
After you left, there was a time…

598
01:13:42,501 --> 01:13:44,670
when I wondered about it every day.

599
01:13:57,642 --> 01:13:58,726
<i>"What if…</i>

600
01:14:00,353 --> 01:14:01,646
<i>I hadn't hesitated that night?"</i>

601
01:14:03,773 --> 01:14:05,024
-Did you make a--
-Excuse me.

602
01:14:31,592 --> 01:14:32,802
Hi, Jong-hyeon.

603
01:14:39,141 --> 01:14:40,518
No, it's fine.

604
01:14:56,367 --> 01:14:58,035
<i>"What if I hadn't turned around?"</i>

605
01:15:29,859 --> 01:15:31,736
<i>"What if I had been open and honest?"</i>

606
01:16:06,854 --> 01:16:08,856
<i>"What if I had told you</i>
<i>not to run away again?"</i>

607
01:16:35,925 --> 01:16:38,177
<i>"What if I had asked you to come with me?"</i>

608
01:16:54,110 --> 01:16:55,236
What about you?

609
01:17:00,658 --> 01:17:02,243
I do wonder sometimes.

610
01:17:33,983 --> 01:17:35,818
I'm sorry for being late, Su-yeong.

611
01:17:39,321 --> 01:17:40,823
It's okay. You're here now.

612
01:17:52,751 --> 01:17:55,045
<i>"What if I had waited a bit longer?"</i>

613
01:17:58,465 --> 01:18:00,259
<i>If I had kept my promise…</i>

614
01:18:02,052 --> 01:18:03,470
<i>that day at the hotel…</i>

615
01:18:09,101 --> 01:18:10,519
would you have dated me?

616
01:18:15,024 --> 01:18:16,567
Actually, I…

617
01:18:20,237 --> 01:18:22,948
Jong-hyeon and I aren't in a relationship.

618
01:18:23,949 --> 01:18:25,826
<i>"What if I had been honest?"</i>

619
01:18:27,828 --> 01:18:29,622
<i>You asked me</i>

620
01:18:29,705 --> 01:18:31,332
at the training institute

621
01:18:33,626 --> 01:18:35,669
if things would've been different for us

622
01:18:36,545 --> 01:18:38,756
had you shown up that day.

623
01:18:44,720 --> 01:18:45,638
<i>I regret…</i>

624
01:18:46,555 --> 01:18:47,765
<i>not telling the truth.</i>

625
01:18:48,474 --> 01:18:49,350
Yes.

626
01:18:51,101 --> 01:18:52,895
Things would've been different.

627
01:18:55,147 --> 01:18:55,981
<i>I like you.</i>

628
01:18:58,734 --> 01:19:01,779
I know I'll sound like a jerk
for saying this right now,

629
01:19:02,363 --> 01:19:03,781
but I'll take that risk.

630
01:19:06,450 --> 01:19:07,576
Ahn Su-yeong,

631
01:19:09,203 --> 01:19:10,329
I like you.

632
01:19:16,585 --> 01:19:17,836
To be honest…

633
01:19:22,800 --> 01:19:24,176
I also

634
01:19:25,844 --> 01:19:27,096
like you.

635
01:19:30,641 --> 01:19:32,685
<i>"What if I had said that I liked you too?"</i>

636
01:19:39,817 --> 01:19:41,235
I don't have to see you off, right?

637
01:20:35,289 --> 01:20:36,540
Let's go together.

638
01:20:50,304 --> 01:20:52,056
<i>"And that I wanted to go with you?"</i>

639
01:21:01,774 --> 01:21:03,317
It's all in the past.

640
01:21:04,443 --> 01:21:07,071
That's why I think of so many what-ifs.

641
01:21:11,116 --> 01:21:14,870
In that case,
how do you think things would've changed?

642
01:21:21,794 --> 01:21:23,420
We might have gotten married.

643
01:21:27,383 --> 01:21:28,717
And had a baby.

644
01:21:32,679 --> 01:21:33,931
And fight at times?

645
01:21:34,556 --> 01:21:38,560
Right. We would've been working parents,

646
01:21:39,686 --> 01:21:42,564
so we would've argued about stuff like,

647
01:21:42,648 --> 01:21:44,858
who would drop off the kid at daycare.

648
01:21:46,860 --> 01:21:49,113
And that could've
eventually led to a divorce.

649
01:21:51,031 --> 01:21:53,367
You always imagine the worst.

650
01:21:56,620 --> 01:21:58,705
There's also a possibility
that we could've made up

651
01:21:58,789 --> 01:22:00,499
and lived happily ever after.

652
01:22:03,710 --> 01:22:05,587
I guess so.

653
01:22:10,426 --> 01:22:11,927
But even in our imaginations…

654
01:22:13,971 --> 01:22:15,472
there's nothing very special.

655
01:22:20,769 --> 01:22:22,146
Isn't that what love is?

656
01:22:24,314 --> 01:22:27,067
Two people going through
everyday life together.

657
01:22:52,384 --> 01:22:53,927
<i>We were once</i>

658
01:22:55,512 --> 01:22:56,889
<i>a part of each other's lives.</i>

659
01:23:05,731 --> 01:23:06,899
<i>We fell for each other.</i>

660
01:23:19,620 --> 01:23:21,246
<i>Our hearts skipped for each other.</i>

661
01:23:32,549 --> 01:23:33,509
<i>We were foolish.</i>

662
01:23:44,144 --> 01:23:45,479
<i>All the moments…</i>

663
01:23:54,154 --> 01:23:55,572
<i>that we regretted made us…</i>

664
01:24:03,288 --> 01:24:05,082
<i>long for each other even more.</i>

665
01:24:15,384 --> 01:24:16,760
<i>During those times…</i>

666
01:24:20,138 --> 01:24:21,306
<i>-Were we…</i>
<i>-Were we…</i>

667
01:24:23,725 --> 01:24:25,185
<i>actually in love…</i>

668
01:24:27,229 --> 01:24:28,772
<i>Or were we blinded by the interest?</i>

669
01:24:40,409 --> 01:24:42,160
What did you forget today?

670
01:24:54,464 --> 01:24:56,216
You said this was the Hill of Oblivion.

671
01:25:01,930 --> 01:25:04,266
So I wondered what you forgot today.

672
01:25:12,691 --> 01:25:13,942
Nothing.

673
01:25:25,370 --> 01:25:26,997
Absolutely nothing.

674
01:26:28,975 --> 01:26:33,605
THE INTEREST OF LOVE

675
01:27:30,537 --> 01:27:35,542
Subtitle translation by: Sooji Kim

